    <title>MAX32-specific GPIO Flags</title>
    <sectiondef kind="user-defined">
      <header>MAX32 GPIO drive flags</header>
      <description><para>MAX32 GPIO drive flags</para>
<para>The drive flags are encoded in the 8 upper bits of <ref refid="group__gpio__interface_1gad435719dccdc37c05852960a7218fbd2" kindref="member">gpio_dt_flags_t</ref> as follows:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Bit 8: GPIO Supply Voltage Select Selects the voltage rail used for the pin. 0: VDDIO 1: VDDIOH</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Bit 9: GPIO Drive Strength Select, MAX32_GPIO_DRV_STRENGTH_0 = 1mA MAX32_GPIO_DRV_STRENGTH_1 = 2mA MAX32_GPIO_DRV_STRENGTH_2 = 4mA MAX32_GPIO_DRV_STRENGTH_3 = 8mA</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Bit 10: Weak pull up selection, Weak Pullup to VDDIO (1MOhm) 0: Disable 1: Enable</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Bit 11: Weak pull down selection, Weak Pulldown to VDDIOH (1MOhm) 0: Disable 1: Enable </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</description>
